    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="39"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mendonça</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of Brazil</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received March 18.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The minister of foreign relations of Brazil, by
                    cable of this date, directs me to communicate to your excellency that the
                    diplomatic relations <pb facs="0108" n="48" xml:id="pg_48"/> between Brazil and
                    Portugal have been reestablished and assigns to me the agreeable duty of
                    offering to the President of the United States the sincerest thanks of the
                    Government of Brazil for the protection extended by the American minister at
                    Lisbon to the Brazilian citizens resident in Portugal and its possessions during
                    the suspension of the diplomatic relations between the two countries.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Salvador de Mendonça</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
